node.text:
"WE'VE GOT TROUBLE HERE!": Two guests at a reptile center near Salt Lake City, Utah, bravely jumped into an enclosure to rescue a handler pulled in by an alligator at a children’s birthday party on Saturday as frightened kids looked on. 

The company said the handler was treated with first aid on scene, then taken to a hospital and is expected to make a full recovery, according to local media reports.

node.title: Zoo guests save reptile handler from gator's jaws

node.text: SUBWAY RESCUE: An @nypd officer and brave Bronx, NY subway riders jumped onto the tracks to save a man who passed out and fell off the station platform, rescuing him just seconds before the train pulled in, according to the NYPD Instagram account on Thursday.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Newsmax on August 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NEWSMAX TALIBAN 'MOCKING' BIDEN WITH PRESS BLITZ AP'.

node.text:
Politicos are doing a double-take after witnessing the strange PR blitz deployed by the Taliban — a terror group responsible for untold atrocities and now in control of Afghanistan — just hours after President Joe Biden briefly emerged to address Kabul’s collapse, refused questions, then departed again for the presidential retreat. ⁣
⁣
For more on this story, click the link in our bio, or visit Newsmax.com⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Newsmax on August 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text.

node.text:
The FBI said Wednesday that its agents are joining a criminal investigation into an alleged security breach of a rural Colorado county's voting equipment. 

For the latest on this story, click the link in bio, or visit Newsmax.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Newsmax in Kabul, Afghanistan. May be an image of one or more people, outdoors and text that says 'Sgt. Isaiah Campbell/U.S Marine Corps AP'.

node.text:
U.S. Army Soldiers assigned to the 10th Mountain Division stand security at Hamid Karzai International Airport, in Kabul, Afghanistan, on Monday. 

U.S. Soldiers and Marines are assisting the Department of State with an orderly drawdown of designated personnel in Afghanistan.

For more coverage of the Afghanistan crisis, click the link in our bio, or visit Newsmax.com.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Newsmax on August 18, 2021. May be a cartoon of 1 person, standing and text that says 'NEWSMAX 2 NEW POLL: VOTERS PREFER TRUMP' S IMMIGRATION POLICY OVER BIDEN'S zz/Dennis Van Tine/STAR MAX/IP'.

node.text:
Forty-five percent of voters say that former President Donald Trump had better immigration policies than President Joe Biden, while 40% prefer the approach of the current president, according to a Scott Rasmussen national survey released on Wednesday.

For more on this story and poll results, click the link in our bio, or visit Newsmax.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Newsmax on August 18, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NEWSMAX REP. MAST TO NEWSMAX: BIDEN 'DOES NOT DESERVE' TO REMAIN IN OFFICE Oliver Contreras/Sipa JSA'.

node.text:
Rep. Brian Mast, a U.S. Army combat veteran who lost both legs in an IED blast while serving in Afghanistan, told Newsmax Tuesday that President Joe Biden "does not deserve to have the titles of commander or chief anywhere close to his name" after the way he has committed the "greatest military blunder in my lifetime's history," with how he has handled the end of the 20-year war, and the mass evacuation efforts from that country.

For more on this story, click the link in our bio, or visit Newsmax.com

node.text:
SCHOOL'S IN SESSION: A diver off the coast of the Maldives remained calm as they floated motionless near the surface of the water while a school of nurse sharks swam around them, footage shared to Instagram shows.

Nurse sharks are, according to National Geographic, “slow-moving bottom-dwellers” that are, “for the most part, harmless to humans”

Greg Kelly: 'Sorry to disturb your vacation, Mister President,' but "this is looking like the fiasco of all fiascos."

via Greg Kelly Reports, weekdays at 7 PM ET on Newsmax:

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Newsmax on August 17, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NEWSMAX BREAKING NEWS TEXAS GOV. GREG ABBOTT TESTS POSITIVE FOR COVID-19 GettyImages/SpencerPlatt'.

node.text:
BREAKING: Fully vaccinated Texas Governor Greg Abbott has tested positive for COVID-19, but he is currently experiencing no symptoms, his office announced. 

"Gov. Abbott is fully vaccinated against COVID-19, in good health, and currently experiencing no symptoms," spokesman Mark Miner wrote in a statement. "Everyone that the governor has been in close contact with today has been notified. Texas first lady Cecilia Abbott tested negative."

Abbott, who has sought to block local officials in the state from mandating the use of masks, has been receiving daily tests for the infection, despite being fully vaccinated and will quarantine at the governor's mansion.

Keep it locked on Newsmax.com for the latest.

node.text:
LOCKDOWN: New Zealand's government took drastic action Tuesday by putting the entire nation into a strict lockdown for at least three days after finding a single case of coronavirus infection in the community. 

For more on this story, click the link in our bio, or visit Newsmax.com
